/**
   @page through-shared-base-pointer-test Writing the test for serializing through a base pointer

If you want to be able to serialize your class through a shared pointer to the base class you
only need to add one line to the test you've already written.

Simply write and add the test file to dataclasses/private/serialization-test.
Your test file will look like...

@verbatim

/**
    copyright  (C) 2004
    the icecube collaboration
    $Id: I3MyClass.cxx 1360 2005-03-31 17:38:00Z troy $

    @version $Revision: 1.1 $
    @date $Date: 2005-03-31 12:38:00 -0500 (Thu, 31 Mar 2005) $
    @author Troy D. Straszheim

*/

#include "serialization-test.h"
#include "dataclasses/I3MyClass.h"

TEST_GROUP(I3MyClass);

I3_SERIALIZATION_TEST(I3MyClass);

I3_VIRTUAL_SERIALIZATION_TEST(I3BaseClass,I3MyClass); //<---This is the only line to add


@endverbatim

By running 'make all-tests-run' you should see the results of the tests.

@verbatim
> make-all-tests-run

...
I3RecoHit...
  binary......................................................   ok
  binary_via_I3Hit............................................   ok
  xml.........................................................   ok
  xml_via_I3Hit...............................................   ok
...

>
@endverbatim

If this test passes you should be able to serialize this class.

*/
